      "id": 941,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:25",
      "content": "Fix task row click-to-jump so it selects the correct agent when navigating to the source message.\n\n**Work inside:** `.synapse/worktrees/developer-25-fix-task-jump-agent`\nCommit your changes to that branch. Do not push.\n\n---\n\n**Problem:**\nWhen clicking a task row, the UI selects the task's owning agent (e.g. worker `:25`) and then jumps to the source message. But the source message (e.g. a human→orchestrator message) lives in a different agent's thread. `document.getElementById('msg-927')` returns null because the message isn't rendered in the worker's message list.\n\n**Fix:**\nThe task row already has `data-source-msg` and `data-trigger-msg` attributes. To know which agent's thread contains the source message, we need to look up the message's `to_id`.\n\n**Option A (preferred — no new API):** Add the source message's `to_id` to the task row as a `data-source-msg-agent` attribute when rendering task rows.\n\nIn `src/dashboard.ts` (or wherever tasks are fetched for the SSE payload), the tasks query already joins with messages. We need to include the `to_id` of the source message in the task payload.\n\nCheck `src/db.ts` for the tasks query (around the `getRecentTasks` or similar function). Add `source_msg_to_id` to the task result by joining with messages:\n\n```sql\nSELECT t.*, m.to_id AS source_msg_to_id \nFROM tasks t\nLEFT JOIN messages m ON t.source_msg_id = m.id\n```\n\nThen in `public/app.js`, when rendering the task row:\n```js\nconst sourceMsgAgent = a.source_msg_to_id ?? '';\n// add to the div:\ndata-source-msg-agent=\"${esc(sourceMsgAgent)}\"\n```\n\nAnd in the click handler (around line 520), use this agent instead of the task owner when navigating:\n```js\nconst targetAgentId = row.dataset.sourceMsgAgent || row.dataset.agentId;\nif (targetAgentId && targetAgentId !== selectedAgentId) {\n  selectedAgentId = targetAgentId;\n  renderAgents();\n  renderMessages();\n  // ...\n}\n```\n\n**Files:** `src/db.ts` (tasks query), `public/app.js` (render + click handler).\n`npm run build` must pass. Commit. Report DONE to cec50b17:0.",
